A motorcyclist who died after a crash involving a four wheel drive vehicle on the A82 near Glencoe has been named as Alasdair Knox, 45, from Tranent, East Lothian. Police name crash victim A motorcyclist who died after a crash involving a four wheel drive vehicle on the A82 near Glencoe has been named as Alasdair Knox, 45, from Tranent, East Lothian.The collision took place shortly after 12:30 on Monday, close to the Glen Etive junction.A man and a woman in the 4x4 were taken to hospital, but were not seriously hurt. 